msgid "By default, FreeBSD includes support for One-time Passwords In Everything (<acronym>OPIE</acronym>). <acronym>OPIE</acronym> is designed to prevent replay attacks, in which an attacker discovers a user's password and uses it to access a system. Since a password is only used once in <acronym>OPIE</acronym>, a discovered password is of little use to an attacker. <acronym>OPIE</acronym> uses a secure hash and a challenge/response system to manage passwords. The FreeBSD implementation uses the <acronym>MD5</acronym> hash by default."
