#. (itstool) path: sect1/para
#: book.translate.xml:24271
msgid "<acronym>OPIE</acronym> uses three different types of passwords. The first is the usual <trademark class=\"registered\">UNIX</trademark> or Kerberos password. The second is the one-time password which is generated by <command>opiekey</command>. The third type of password is the <quote>secret password</quote> which is used to generate one-time passwords. The secret password has nothing to do with, and should be different from, the <trademark class=\"registered\">UNIX</trademark> password."
